    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Waist-length jackets of denim or other twill cotton with panel stitching and patch pockets in front.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000013151/Esquire's Encyclopedia of 20th C. Men's Fashions (1973)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Chaqueta informal que llega hasta la altura de la cintura, de denim u otro tejido de algodón cruzado, con un panel punteado y bolsillos de parches en la parte delantera.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Spanish</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000131/CDBP-SNPC</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000051034/TAA database (2000-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Jasjes tot in de taille van denim of ander keperkatoen, vaak blauw, waarbij de patroondelen worden geaccentueerd met stiksels, met opgestikte zakken aan de voorkant, waarvan sommige delen, b.v. de zakken, bij de hoeken worden versterkt met klinknagels.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000205/AAT-Ned</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
